I won't argue, that sounds horrible.

I had these points in my life actually. When I was a bit younger, I was, _believe me or not_, gay. That's right, people! I was gay! Of course, I didn't tell anyone about this. As I grew older, I started to mature and understand the world better and then I noticed the things people do to break any transgendered ideals and one-way marriages. Of course, I stopped being gay and instead became bisexual because it was easier to me.

Why I was gay, some might ask? I was a feminine lad and I hang out with female lads. I didn't like how boys acted when I was young and I liked how girls were actually caring instead of idiotic. Sure, I have males as friends but I wasn't that close to them. Hanging out with girls only shaped a bit of myself.

Too bad nothing goes the way you wanted it to go. Boys or girls, people aren't always that accepting.
